== Basmati Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the
@Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid and leave
to the side until ready to serve.

== Halloumi Curry ==

While the rice cooks, drain the @Halloumi{225%g}, then cut it into roughly 1cm chunks.

Heat a large #frying pan with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, turning frequently, ~{3-4%mins}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press).

Once the halloumi is golden, lower the heat to medium and add another drizzle of
@oil{drizzle} to the pan.

Add the garlic and @Korma Curry Paste{50%g}. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%min}.

Pour the @Chopped Tomatoes{1}(with onion and garlic), @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g},
@Red Pepper Chilli Jelly{25%g} and @Sugar{1} for the sauce into the pan.
Stir to combine.

Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{5-6%mins}.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping
hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir through half the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%g}, then taste and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and top with the halloumi curry.

Finish with a dollop of the remaining yoghurt on top. Enjoy!

